{"title": "Villain Shoes", "content": "An instance, generally restricted to video games, wherein the player gets to control the villain for a short period of time, as opposed to the hero. This doesn't apply to spin-off games or multiplayer modes, or being a Villain Protagonist; it only counts if it takes place during the course of the story. This is often done to give the player a Taste of Power, especially if the villain is the Big Bad himself or far more powerful than the player character. If done well, this also establishes that the villain could kill you with his pinky finger without having to see him do it to you. Sometimes, it may involve with a Perspective Flip in which you can learn his motives behind his villainy.\n\nCompare Villain Episode, when an episodic series gives the villain A Day in the Limelight. If your current Player Character turns out to be the villain in the sequel, this is Rogue Protagonist, which may or may not involve with Dueling Player Characters.\n\nA subversion of No Campaign for the Wicked. Doesn't have to involve literal shoes, but it helps.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainShoes", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamAsylum", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamOrigins", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamKnight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ShadowOfTheColossus", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheForceUnleashed", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/RogueSquadron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/UltimateSpiderMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SpiderMan1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HyruleWarriors", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Halo2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PerfectDark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CallOfDutyBlackOpsII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CrashOfTheTitans", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarTrekArmada", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarCraftI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Warcraft", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/V